Overall PE figure for the isalnd of Gozo was estimated on the basis of the total domestic population, industry connected, seasonal tourism statistics, seasonal water consumption and analysis of sewage grab samples. An over estimation of about 15% was allowed for, during sizing of the UWWTP.

Overall PE figure for the 'Rest of Malta' (i.e. Malta South and Marsa Land) was estimated on the bases of the domestic population, seasonal tourism, industry, seasonal water consumption and analysis of sewage grab samples. An 18% reserve campacity by load was allowed for, in the sizing of the UWWTP. The Marsa Land agglomeration load was then estimated on the basis of the total estimated 'Rest of Malta' PE load x (ratio of the water comsumption of the Marsa Land agglomeration to that of the 'Rest of Malta' agglomeration).

Overall PE figure for the Malta North agglomeration was estimated on the bases of the domestic population, seasonal, tourism, seasonal water consumption and analysis of sewage grab samples. A 10% reserve capacity by load was allowed for, in the sizing of the UWWTP.
The Malta South was calculated on the basis of the total estimated 'Rest of Malta' PE load x (water consumption of Malta South aggolmeration to that of the 'Rest of Malta')
